No, it seems not. The creature growled only and tried to fly directly at Thassalin. Luckily, Thassalin was agile enough despite his size and dodged, but Nyssi let out a cry as she narrowly lost her grip on Thassalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill you?" Nyssi screamed.
"AIM AT THEIR HEADS!"
"This will be difficult!"
Thassalin hissed and then drew a circle, closer to the mountain, which he called his home. The dark beast followed but became slightly panicked when it was hit from behind by a fire beam. It hadn't noticed that it was no longer alone. It became even more panicked when Thassalin slowed down and then hurled his tail against its head, deflecting it off course.
Growling and snarling, she flew upwards and spat into the air. Suddenly everything became dark, as if the monster was sucking the light out of the sky into itself and replacing it with a cloud of eternal night.
As he suddenly couldn't see anything anymore, Thassalin tried to retreat. He felt himself sliding along the treetops before he eventually fell into a clearing. The beast seemed to know exactly where he had fallen and shot straight towards him, dragging the black cloud with it.
"Tenuk!" screamed, as he slipped out of the cloud and began to circle, looking down into the darkness for Nyssi and Thassalin. "What are we to do now? Kayel…? Kayel, where are you?"
Below, Nyssi laboriously came to her feet. She was sure she had broken something, but her strange, supernatural healing powers were already taking effect. Unfortunately, this did not apply to Thassalin. He leaned exhausted against the only tree that had not collapsed under his weight. Nyssi made a great effort to get near Thassalin, but she could hardly see two meters. Everything was pitch black and shrouded in eerie shadows. And in this shadow, something screamed and shrieked.
A terrifying, armoured tail crashed down beside Nyssi and brought her to the ground. However, she noticed that the tail was wildly thrashing about and not trying to deliberately hit her. The beast, or whatever it was that Nyssi could see and hear of it, growled and swiped at the shadows it had created. Something shot through the darkness, struck the monster and disoriented it.
Suddenly a rifle shot crashed through the fog, and the monster fell silent, collapsed to the ground and lay motionless. The darkness around them dissolved, and they saw what had happened: On the beast stood Kayel, who was heavily panting, holding his rifle.
"That was probably... The craziest shadow leap I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon...", Kabel gasped for air. His eyes glowed almost black, and a dark energy swirled around his body. But as he still spoke, the color returned to his armor, and his eyes regained their normal yellow color.
It took a moment for Nyssi to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed these strange shadow powers. He rarely used them, because most people found them unsettling and quite intimidating. But Nyssi hadn't known that Kayel could also use these powers in any kind of darkness. And the way Kayel was acting, he seemed to be quite surprised as well.
"Are you okay?", Nyssi burst out.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something, I'll be in order again soon." Kayel looked at his work, as Tenuk fell down, landed beside him, and returned to its normal Spat form.
Now that the beast was no longer moving, they could see what it was better. Its skin was raven-black and slimy, but the slime remained stuck to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, all ending in long, thin claws, and two straight horns protruded from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what the devil those two had in front of them, something shrieked and sprang out of a nearby bush. However, it didn't reach them because a familiar vehicle crashed into its side and ensured that the monster slid to a stop in front of Nyssi's feet. Nyssi wasn't willing to take a risk. She grabbed her shotgun, shot without thinking at its head, and the creature died right there.
"Oops...", Retvik muttered from the driver's seat before turning off the engine unsteadily and stepping out of the truck. "Uh, that wasn't actually intended. Are you all okay?"
"You've missed the whole action," Tenuk scolded. "Where were you?"
"You've all just left me standing here. I came as fast as I could...", sighed Retvik. "May I ask, what are those dreadful creatures?"
Retvik's question was fortunately answered by Thassalin, who had picked himself up again. He was covered in cuts and scratches and seemed a little dazed, but not too seriously hurt.
"YOU HAVE KILLED THE CORRUPT ONES! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. BEINGS, WHO ARE LEAVING HERE, AS CORRUPTION ATTACKS YOUR GODS."
"You mean the dreadful God-monster creature that we... helped to kill?", stammered Tenuk.
"YES. EXACTLY THAT. MAYBE THERE'S EVEN MORE. BUT I COULDN'T THINK IT UP. I DON'T HAVE A GUN. AND TWO AGAINST ONE IS UNFAIR, OR?"
"Ah... thanks... I think...", Kayel shrugged with his shoulders. "So, are we done here then?"
Nysse hunched her shoulders. She snatched up her camera and took a few photos of the beasts, now definitely dead. Then she drew her favorite weapon, the decorated Totentanz dagger, and began cutting off one of the beast's horns. After that, she went to the second one. But just as Nysse finished, the beasts suddenly burst into flames and in the blink of an eye turned into a pile of ashes. The same thing happened to the horns Nysse had cut off.
"So, that's practically and unpractically at the same time...," sighed Nyssi. "But at least I have the photos, hopefully."
